The Nelson Mandela Bay chamber evacuated the UDM&#8217;s Mongameli Bobani as representative chairman on Thursday.The official count was 60 votes for the movement by Patriotic Alliance councilor Marlon Daniels to evacuate Bobani.The parties that supported the motion were the DA COPE and ACDP.Daniels said Bobani was disruptive and was creating instability in the metro.Opposition parties have however refused to accept the result as they had been walking out of the council chamber while voting on the motion was taking place. Loading...